If you ignore the actual sketch and listen to the Nazi Officer he really does tell a pretty awesome story. So the other day he's at the local market buying some bread when he notices Hitler and Eva (who is taller than you might think) doing the same thing. As he is rarely up close to Hitler, he also notices that, being near the weekend, the little hairs on either side of Hitler's mustache are starting to grow in. Someone definitely needs a fresh shave! So, the Officer greets Hitler with a standard salute and is stoked when Hitler returns with a down-low half salute, all cool-like, then he realizes how funny it is that Hitler doesn't say "Heil Hitler" back like he's used to hearing from everyone else. Starting some small talk, the Officer tells Hitler that he's been quite busy, and is delighted to hear Hitler chuckle with the response, "you and me both". What a sense of humor! Finally, if that wasn't enough, the best part of the story reveals that as Hitler begins to leave, he remarks, "Well, there's no point in getting bread if you're not going to get..." Then he and the Nazi Officer both say "cheese" at the same time, look to each other and both yell "Jinx!" Just like a couple of normal guys! I think it's an awesome story and would've have kept interrupting like the Nazi Cadet did.

For anyone that somehow manages to make it to the bottom of this comment thread, what the apologists and obvious Nazis above me won't tell you is why the Nazis recruited Non-Aryans and in what roles they served. For some background on Nazi views in recruitment of Non-Aryans in the early war when they were not suffering very severe manpower shortages, when colonial troops of France fought against Nazi onslaught and were captured, they were overwhelmingly shot on the spot by regular German units. Not the SS, regular army units would shoot them. This fantasy idea that these proponents tout that somehow the Nazis were accepting of Africans is a product of Olympic levels of mental gymnastics. While Mein Kampf does not touch on relations with Africans at length because his ambitions were in Europe, he does speak of them in the same vein of the Jews, and advocates their destruction. Related to this is the 1938 Nuremberg laws passed by Hitler, which among other things, banned non-Aryans from "reaping the benefits of the German state" which meant that all non-Germans could not use any public service or be a public servant. This by extension means that no non-Aryans were allowed in the Army. Now what you will see these apologists point to is the very small SS units, which were part of the political branch of the Nazi government. These units were often undertrained and made of conscripts, unlike what Hollywood would have you believe (As a side, most all SS units were just as poorly trained as their Army counterparts by 1943-44, just more fanatical). These SS units were recruited to fill holes were German manpower was running out, especially by 1943-44, where you see most of the recruitment of Non-Aryans when severe manpower shortages were deeply effecting the effectiveness of all branches of Military. These units were not respected, not treated well, under-equipped and often sent on the most dangerous work of the fronts while trying to keep them operating in the nation's they were raised from if possible. The notion that the Nazis weren't racist in is purely fantastical, and the proponents of this myth often have ulterior motive for spouting it other than just ignorance.

Â @BiggieSmalls574Â  the SS was a section of the Nazi party, membership was mostly restricted to persons who could prove "Aryan" purity back several generations. The Waffen -SS, however was the ARMED units of the SS and was composed of conscripts and volunteers from German colonies, occupied lands, enemy POW's, foreign mercenaries, minor allied nations (Germany's allies) and many from European colonies or territories who the Nazis promised to help with independence from their European colonisers. So there were African blacks from German African colonies, Arabs, Chinese, Indians, Japanese, Italians, Turks, Balkans, Russians, all sorts of Asians, other Europeans, Pacific Islanders etc. There were also black Germans and Jewish Germans in both the Waffen SS and regular German military. No Blue ChairsÂ  Other way around. People started out dark-skinned and some populations changed as they migrated to new areas. Here, a nice simple timeline  1. From about 1.2 million years ago to less than 100,000 years ago, archaic humans, including archaic Homo sapiens, were dark-skinned.  2. As Homo sapiens populations began to migrate, the evolutionary constraint keeping skin dark decreased proportionally to the distance north a population migrated, resulting in a range of skin tones within northern populations.  3. At some point, some northern populations experienced positive selection for lighter skin due to the increased production of vitamin D from sunlight and the genes for darker skin disappeared from these populations.  4. Subsequent migrations into different UV environments and admixture between populations have resulted in the varied range of skin pigmentations we see today.
